\documentclass{article}
\title{Test of the T1 package option}
\usepackage[enable-debug]{expl3}
\usepackage[T1]{nyu22fonts}
\begin{document}
\maketitle

This test checks if the \texttt{nyu22fonts} package with the
\texttt{T1} option works. The expected behavior is that sans
serif fonts select from the Helvetica family, while serif
fonts come from Charter.

Type 1 fonts require the pdftex engine. Xetex and Luatex
can't find them. So for now this test only succeeds on the
one engine.

\ExplSyntaxOn
\debug_on:n { check-declarations , deprecation }

\tl_set:Nn \l_tmpa_tl {Mr.~Jock,~TV~quiz~PhD.,~bags~few~lynx.}

\clist_set:Nn \l_tmpa_clist
  {
    \sffamily,
    \sffamily\bfseries,
    \sffamily\itshape,
    \rmfamily,
    \rmfamily\bfseries,
    \rmfamily\itshape
  }

\START

\clist_map_inline:Nn \l_tmpa_clist 
  {
    \TEST{#1}
      {
        \hbox_set:Nn \l_tmpa_box {#1 \tl_use:N \l_tmpa_tl}
        \box_show:N \l_tmpa_box
        \box_use:N \l_tmpa_box
      }    
  }
\ExplSyntaxOff
\end{document}
